    "body": "@0xalex88 this issue is about block rewards rather than attestation rewards, so it's a different bug (if a bug at all)\r\n\r\nI think actually it isn't a bug, because that validator _did_ fail to match head in epoch 254430. They attested to the block from 2 slots prior (https://beaconcha.in/slot/20433f2c22faa6707f104f44ce227f6cb6e51e029073946ce06483f5f7827d34), i.e. attesting to slot 8141758 at slot 8141760.\r\n\r\nThe reason the balance change from epoch 30 -> 31 doesn't show the penalty is that the rewards for attestations in epoch N are applied at the transition from N + 1 to N + 2 (because attestations for the previous epoch can be included for all of epoch N + 1). So we see the balance diff between 31 and 32:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -s \"http://localhost:5052/eth/v1/beacon/states/8141792/validator_balances?id=1073492\" | jq\r\n```\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"execution_optimistic\": false,\r\n  \"finalized\": true,\r\n  \"data\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"index\": \"1073492\",\r\n      \"balance\": \"32014336347\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -s \"http://localhost:5052/eth/v1/beacon/states/8141824/validator_balances?id=1073492\" | jq\r\n```\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"execution_optimistic\": false,\r\n  \"finalized\": true,\r\n  \"data\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"index\": \"1073492\",\r\n      \"balance\": \"32014334078\"\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe difference is `32014334078 - 32014336347 = -2269`. This matches the rewards API: `-4888 + 2619 = -2269`.",
